NUMBER 333
NAME Church of Shemri, narthex
REGION 205
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The narthex, a sort of entry hall for the church, is painted white and
laboriously trimmed in blue scrollwork resembling nothing more than frothy
waves. Two tiled pillars rise into an archway leading into the church
proper and overhead is a model of the planets and the sun, showing Andor
to be in the center.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT O 242
IFPREVERB POINT -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 163
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her thanks to you quickly.
    ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her thanks.
    ADD SHEMCOPPER ITEMVAL1
    REMOVEITEM -1
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 162
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her thanks to you.
    ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her thanks.
    ADD SHEMSILVER ITEMVAL1
    REMOVEITEM -1
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER A young priestess takes the donation, bowing her profuse thanks to you.
    ECHO OTHERS A young priestess takes %n's donation, bowing her profuse thanks.
    ADD SHEMGOLD ITEMVAL1
    REMOVEITEM -1
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SHEMCOPPER > 10
    EQUAL FLAG4 SHEMCOPPER
    DIV FLAG4 10
    ADD SHEMSILVER FLAG4
    MOD SHEMCOPPER 10
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SHEMSILVER > 10
    EQUAL FLAG4 SHEMSILVER
    DIV FLAG4 10
    ADD SHEMGOLD FLAG4
    MOD SHEMSILVER 10
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SHEMGOLD > 0
    ADD PVAL86 SHEMGOLD
    EQUAL SHEMGOLD 0
  ENDIF
  IFVAR PVAL86 > 5000
    SUB PVAL86 5000
    ADD PVAL87 5
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
ITEM 0 60 VAL2=1151
ITEM 1 248
;model
EXTEND 1 of the planets and sun
ITEM 2 411
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The tiny tiles are carefully fitted into mosaic images of growth and birth, flowers blooming, grapevines overrunning the arbor and animals of the field loading or nursing young. At the apex of the arch appears the image of a smiling woman whose radia
nce touches each of the other images and somehow completes them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB TURN 1
	ECHO ALL It makes a tinkling sound.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR ALIGN < -5
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You hear a voice in your mind, "Your presence is not desired here, dark one."
    ADD FLAG4 5
    DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 1 You are picked and gently put on the ground.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME FLAG4
    ECHO OTHERS %n moves towards the door, but is picked up, stretched out prone and lowered to the street!
    POSITION LAY
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ALIGN > 0
    ECHO PLAYER You hear a gentle touch on your mind, "Welcome to my home, stay in peace and Light."
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ALIGN > -4
    IFVAR ALIGN < 1
      ECHO PLAYER You are mildly chided "You are walking between the dark and the light.
      ECHO PLAYER Seek to cleanse yourself in your travels ahead."
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
